parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear on the steer tires can lead to reduced traction, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of tire failure, which can cause accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Uneven tire wear on the right side
premature wear on the steer tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the kingpins can cause the wheels to wobble, leading to premature tire wear, reduced traction, and increased risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Wheels wobble
kingpins will not hold their adjustment
premature steer tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the U-bolts on the rear spring hanger can cause vibration, shaking, and noise, which can lead to reduced vehicle stability and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vibration
shaking
cracking
and popping noise under the cab.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Seizure of the windshield wiper control arms can cause the windshield wiper motor to burn out, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wiper control arms seized
windshield wiper motor burned out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air conditioning condenser can cause refrigerant leaks, reducing the effectiveness of the air conditioning system and potentially causing damage to other components.
symptoms: Broken condenser leaking refrigerant under the sleeper inside the right storage compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wiring harness failure can cause a range of electrical system malfunctions, leading to issues with vehicle performance, safety features, and potentially even engine stalling or failure.
symptoms: Flickering or dimming headlights
faulty or inoperable accessories
intermittent electrical system failures
burning smell or smoke from the dashboard or engine compartment
engine stalling or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Dim or failed instrument cluster lighting can reduce the driver's ability to monitor vital vehicle systems, such as speed, fuel level, and engine performance, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: Dim or faint dashboard lights
some dashboard lights not functioning
inconsistent lighting brightness
lights flickering or flashing
complete loss of dashboard lighting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning condenser can cause the loss of cooling performance, leading to discomfort and potential heat-related health issues for the occupants. The leakage of refrigerant can also contribute to ozone depletion and environmental harm.
symptoms: The air conditioner is not blowing cold air
the air conditioner is not functioning properly
refrigerant is leaking from the condenser
the condenser is damaged or broken
the condenser is shaking or vibrating excessively.

symptoms: The air conditioner is not functioning properly
refrigerant is leaking from the condenser
the condenser is damaged or broken
the condenser is shaking or vibrating excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning dashboard can cause distraction, confusion, and decreased visibility while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard lights or gauges are not functioning properly
the dashboard display is dim or flickering
